com.ostrichemulators.semtool.rdf.engine.util

Class QaChecker

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ostrichemulators.semtool.rdf.engine.util.QaChecker

  • public class QaChecker
extends Object
    A class to check for QA errors given a Loading Sheet and an Engine. Basically, this class is just a set of caches with accessor methods. It was lifted from the EngineLoader class to simplify that class.
    Author:
    ryan

      • separateConformanceErrors

        public void separateConformanceErrors(ImportData data,
                                      ImportData errors,
                                      IEngine engine)
        Separates any non-conforming data from the loading data. This removes the offending data from data and puts them in errors
        Parameters:
        data - the data to check for errors
        errors - where to put non-conforming data. If null, this function does nothing
        engine - the engine to check against

        Parameters:

        Returns:

      • checkConformance

        public List<LoadingSheetData.LoadingNodeAndPropertyValues> checkConformance(LoadingSheetData data,
                                                                            IEngine eng,
                                                                            boolean loadcaches)
        Checks conformance of the given data. The data argument will be updated when errors are found. Only relationship data can be non-conforming.
        Parameters:
        data - the data to check
        eng - the engine to check against. Can be null if loadcaches is false
        loadcaches - call #loadCaches(gov.va.semoss.rdf.engine.api.IEngine) first
        Returns:
        a list of all LoadingSheetData.LoadingNodeAndPropertyValues that fail the check

        Checks for an instance of the given type and label. #loadCaches(gov.va.semoss.rdf.engine.api.IEngine) MUST be called prior to this function to have any hope at a true result
        Parameters:
        type -
        label -
        Returns:
        true, if the type/label matches a cached value
